data.content:
The root cause is that `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` 10.0 depends on **Microsoft.OpenApi v2**, which has several breaking changes. Here are the four issues in your code and the fixes:

### 1. `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` namespace removed
All `IOpenApiAny` types (`OpenApiString`, etc.) are replaced by `System.Text.Json.Nodes`.

### 2. `OpenApiSecurityScheme.Reference` / `OpenApiReference` replaced
Dedicated reference types like `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference` now replace setting a `Reference` property manually.

### 3. `OpenApiSecurityRequirement` no longer inherits `Dictionary`
Use its `Schemes` property instead of collection-initializer syntax.

### 4. `Schema.Nullable` removed
Nullability is now expressed via the `Type` flags enum (`JsonSchemaType`). Remove the `Null` flag instead of setting `Nullable = false`.

---

### Corrected code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;              // replaces Microsoft.OpenApi.Any
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References;  // for OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        // OpenApiString → JsonValue.Create()
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    operation.Responses?.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    // OpenApiSecurityScheme + OpenApiReference → OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference
    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");

    // OpenApiSecurityRequirement is no longer a Dictionary — use .Schemes
    operation.Security =
    [
        new OpenApiSecurityRequirement
        {
            Schemes = new Dictionary<OpenApiSecurityScheme, IList<string>>
            {
                [oAuthScheme] = scopes
            }
        }
    ];

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
                // Nullable property removed — clear the Null flag from the Type enum
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

### Summary of changes

| .NET 9 (OpenApi v1) | .NET 10 (OpenApi v2) |
|---|---|
| `using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` | `using System.Text.Json.Nodes` |
| `new OpenApiString("1.0")` | `JsonValue.Create("1.0")` |
| `new OpenApiSecurityScheme { Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" } }` | `new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2")` |
| `new OpenApiSecurityRequirement { [scheme] = scopes }` | `new OpenApiSecurityRequirement { Schemes = new Dictionary<...> { [scheme] = scopes } }` |
| `schema.Nullable = false` | `schema.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null` |
